'''Paul M. Grøstad''' (21 September 1933 – 4 April 2011) was a Norwegian businessperson.

He took the [[cand.jur.]] degree, and worked in [[Norske Shell]] ([[Royal Dutch Shell]] in Norway) from 1960 to 1993. He is best known as the chairman of the company, from 1997 to 2003.<ref name=obit1>{{cite news|title=Paul M. Grøstad (obituary)|page=|last=Laughman|first=David|date=14 April 2011|work=[[Aftenposten]]|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref name=obit2>{{cite news|title=Paul M. Grøstad (obituary)|page=|last=Teien|first=Finn|author2=Østrem, Ragnar|date=14 April 2011|work=[[Aftenposten]]|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

During his time in Norske Shell, he was involved in both building up and closing down the oil refinery in [[Sola]]. The company also became involved in the [[Ormen Lange (gas field)|Ormen Lange]] gas field, eventually becoming the field operator. Grøstad also handled a boycott of Shell, which started because of alleged corporation with apartheid-era South Africa.<ref name=obit1/><ref>{{cite news|title=– Urettferdig aksjon|page=10|last=Vatne|first=Paul Einar|date=22 September 1993|work=[[Aftenposten]]|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

